00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:34,666
to be paid every ten days.

240
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:37,291
And if you can't pay, you'll
be our manservant forever!

241
00:11:37,375 --> 00:11:39,500
Ah crap, I knew this
was too good to be true!

242
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:40,625
Obviously it was...

243
00:11:40,708 --> 00:11:42,916
And now you're our
manservant for life!

244
00:11:44,250 --> 00:11:45,333
That was you?

245
00:11:45,416 --> 00:11:46,916
Don't worry about
us right now, Nagasumi.

246
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,125
We're fine, ya see.

247
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:49,958
Just go find that girl
with the glasses, okay?

248
00:11:50,041 --> 00:11:51,458
We'll kill you!

249
00:11:51,541 --> 00:11:53,083
[SUN] Ya see, ya looked like ya
wanted to swim too, Lunar.

250
00:11:53,166 --> 00:11:54,416
This is payback!

251
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,416
[LUNAR] Come back here, you!

252
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,041
[NAGASUMI] Hey, stop it you two!

253
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:59,250
Maybe mermaids just
need to swim sometimes.

254
00:12:00,625 --> 00:12:02,208
[NAGASUMI] Sorry for the wait!

255
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:07,000
[NAGASUMI] Sorry again.
I only have a credit card.

256
00:12:07,083 --> 00:12:08,208
[NAGASUMI] Do you
think you could come

257
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:10,500
with me to an eyeglasses shop?

258
00:12:10,583 --> 00:12:11,958
Oh, sure, that's fine,

259
00:12:12,041 --> 00:12:13,958
but you don't have to
go to all this trouble.

260
00:12:14,041 --> 00:12:15,333
[NAGASUMI] No, it's no trouble.

261
00:12:15,416 --> 00:12:16,625
[CLASS REP THINKS] Hmm...

262
00:12:16,708 --> 00:12:18,708
There's something
familiar about his voice.

263
00:12:18,791 --> 00:12:21,916
It kinda reminds
me of Nagasumi's...

264
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:24,000
[CLASS REP THINKS] Nah...

265
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:26,166
Nagasumi's out on his
big double date right now.

266
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:29,125
What would he be
doing here in the park?

267
00:12:29,208 --> 00:12:31,041
[NAGASUMI] Is there
something the matter?

268
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:32,458
[CLASS REP] Oh no,
it's nothing really.

269
00:12:32,541 --> 00:12:34,916
Your voice just sounds
like someone I know.

270
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,083
[NAGASUMI] Yeah?

271
00:12:36,166 --> 00:12:38,166
Tell me about this guy,
so what's he like?

272
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:39,583
[CLASS REP] Well there's
this good friend of mine

273
00:12:39,666 --> 00:12:41,166
who has wanted
to be a police officer

274
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:43,041
ever since she was a little kid.

275
00:12:43,125 --> 00:12:44,583
[NAGASUMI] Oh...

276
00:12:44,666 --> 00:12:46,416
You know, I actually have a
friend who's exactly like that.

277
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:47,958
What a coincidence.

278
00:12:48,041 --> 00:12:50,041
And then there's this boy who's
a childhood friend of hers.

279
00:12:50,125 --> 00:12:52,208
It's his voice that
yours reminds me of.

280
00:12:52,291 --> 00:12:54,416
[NAGASUMI] Ah, so this
guy's a friend of a friend?

281
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:58,166
A type of distant acquaintance
situation is that it?

282
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:03,208
Distant? I guess so, more
of an acquaintance.

283
00:13:03,291 --> 00:13:04,875
[CLASS REP] But there's
something about him.

284
00:13:04,958 --> 00:13:06,291
I don't know.

285
00:13:06,375 --> 00:13:09,583
He isn't particularly
attractive or anything, but...

286
00:13:09,666 --> 00:13:10,708
When he talks, his good

287
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:12,458
personality really
shines through.

288
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:14,958
And he can be very kind,
especially to people who are

289
00:13:15,041 --> 00:13:16,833
weaker than him and need help.

290
00:13:16,916 --> 00:13:19,583
And lately he's
been maturing a little.

291
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:22,083
Becoming more
of a man every day.

292
00:13:24,166 --> 00:13:25,500
My heart kinda starts racing

293
00:13:25,583 --> 00:13:27,875
whenever I'm talking about him,
you know what I mean?

294
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:30,625
That's interesting.
So, do you love him?

295
00:13:30,708 --> 00:13:32,125
Wh-Wh-What
are you talking about?

296
00:13:32,208 --> 00:13:33,583
I never said anything like that!
No way! Love! No! Not me.

297
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:35,208
Whoa...
She's an open book.

298
00:13:35,291 --> 00:13:36,583
[NAGASUMI] Listen,
you have to live every

299
00:13:36,666 --> 00:13:38,666
day of your life so
you'll have no regrets.

300
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:41,208
Because you never know
when your life's going to end!

301
00:13:41,291 --> 00:13:42,625
[CLASS REP] Huh?

302
00:13:42,708 --> 00:13:44,000
For all you know, tomorrow
you could be chased around

303
00:13:44,083 --> 00:13:46,000
by an over protective
father wielding a big knife,

304
00:13:46,083 --> 00:13:47,791
or abandoned in a
dungeon for days at a time,

305
00:13:47,875 --> 00:13:50,833
never knowing when you
might be drowned in the bay!

306
00:13:51,208 --> 00:13:53,875
Sorry... It seems I lost my
cool there for a little bit.

307
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:55,833
Please disregard
what I just said.

308
00:13:55,916 --> 00:13:56,750
[CLASS REP] Right.

309
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:58,208
Anyway, my point
is that you can

310
00:13:58,291 --> 00:14:00,500
only do what you want to do
while you're still alive.

311
00:14:00,583 --> 00:14:02,041
You gotta at least try.

312
00:14:02,125 --> 00:14:04,291
Yes... Yes,
I think you're right.

313
00:14:04,375 --> 00:14:06,416
[CLASS REP THINKS]
I wonder if I love Nagasumi.

314
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:09,208
I keep feeling
this pain in my chest.

315
00:14:09,291 --> 00:14:13,416
Is this what they call love?
This ache that won't go away?

316
00:14:14,916 --> 00:14:17,958
[respirator sound]

317
00:14:21,875 --> 00:14:24,000
[KAI THINKS] Come ta think
of it, this is the first time

318
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:26,458
I've been alone with
a girl other than Sun.

319
00:14:26,541 --> 00:14:27,708
[MAWARI THINKS]
Come to think of it,

320
00:14:27,791 --> 00:14:29,333
this might be the
first time I've ever been

321
00:14:29,416 --> 00:14:31,833
alone with a boy
other than Nagasumi.

322
00:14:35,125 --> 00:14:36,791
[MAWARI THINKS]
Mikawa's breathing really hard.

323
00:14:36,875 --> 00:14:39,416
We're in a boat
with no one around.

324
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:42,666
[MAWARI THINKS] All alone.
A young boy and a young girl.

325
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:44,250
Which equals...

326
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:46,291
[VOICES] You're my friend,
but you look tasty!

327
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:48,708
You come any closer and I'll
arrest you for indecency!

328
00:14:48,791 --> 00:14:49,416
Stay right there!

329
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:50,958
[KAI] Huh?

330
00:14:51,041 --> 00:14:52,541
[KAI] Hey, Mawari,
that's dangerous!

331
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:54,750
Ya need ta sit
back down quickly!

332
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:56,541
I swear that
I will arrest you Kai!

333
00:14:56,625 --> 00:14:57,583
[Kai cries out]

334
00:14:57,666 --> 00:14:58,791
[KAI] What're you doing?

335
00:14:58,875 --> 00:15:01,083
[Kai and Mawari cry out]

336
00:15:02,916 --> 00:15:04,250
[CHIMP THINKS] My lord.

337
00:15:13,583 --> 00:15:15,791
Oh, holy crap!
Are you okay?

338
00:15:16,416 --> 00:15:17,541
[CLASS REP] I'm so sorry!

339
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,541
Without my glasses,
I can't see anything.

340
00:15:19,625 --> 00:15:20,625
[NAGASUMI] Well here...

341
00:15:20,708 --> 00:15:22,291
Why don't you hold
onto my arm then?

342
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:24,000
[CLASS REP] Thank you.

343
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:27,708
[CLASS REP THINKS]
I can't ever let Nagasumi

344
00:15:27,791 --> 00:15:30,750
see me look this
clumsy and pathetic.

345
00:15:31,083 --> 00:15:32,541
As far as I'm concerned,
the guy you like

346
00:15:32,625 --> 00:15:34,833
would just be
lucky to have you.

347
00:15:35,291 --> 00:15:37,125
Why don't you just
tell him how you feel?

348
00:15:37,208 --> 00:15:38,291
No. No,
I can't do that!

349
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:39,541
A cute girl like you shouldn't

350
00:15:39,625 --> 00:15:41,333
have any trouble
snagging some guy.

351
00:15:41,416 --> 00:15:43,583
Take it from me.
I guarantee it!

352
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:48,458
Thank you for saying that.
That gives me some confidence.

353
00:15:53,125 --> 00:15:55,375
[NAGASUMI] The eyeglasses
shop is this way, isn't it?

354
00:15:55,458 --> 00:15:57,958
[CLASS REP] It's just a
little past the athletic field.

355
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,708
It sounds real
lively down there.

356
00:16:00,791 --> 00:16:01,916
Is there some sort of boys'

357
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,750
baseball game going
on or something?

358
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:05,000
No, I don't think so.

359
00:16:05,083 --> 00:16:06,583
It looks like a bunch
of old guys are playing.

360
00:16:06,666 --> 00:16:08,291
Come on now!
We can't lose.

361
00:16:08,375 --> 00:16:10,666
Knock it outta the park!
Crush that ball!

362
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:11,500
[NAGASUMI] Oh no!
Not them!

363
00:16:11,583 --> 00:16:12,958
Crush that ball!

364
00:16:13,916 --> 00:16:18,333
Boss, take a look at the
top of the hill! Gyo!

365
00:16:18,416 --> 00:16:20,583
Boss it's that snot
nosed maggot! Gyo!

366
00:16:20,666 --> 00:16:21,875
Walking with a chick!

367
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:23,208
Could it be we've caught
him red handed

368
00:16:23,291 --> 00:16:25,208
cheating on your
beautiful daughter?

369
00:16:25,291 --> 00:16:27,541
[GOZABURO] Nab him right now!

370
00:16:27,625 --> 00:16:28,625
Alright...

371
00:16:28,708 --> 00:16:30,333
Now let's drown
the maggot in the river.

372
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:31,791
Yes sir, boss sir.

373
00:16:31,875 --> 00:16:33,375
[NAGASUMI] I'm gonna drown!
Someone help me!

374
00:16:33,458 --> 00:16:34,416
[CLASS REP] No, don't!

375
00:16:35,458 --> 00:16:36,750
Please understand...

376
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:39,041
...that boy was only trying
to replace my glasses.

377
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:40,333
That's all that it was...

378
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:43,083
I promise you, we haven't
done anything wrong.

379
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:44,916
Wait a second.

380
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,583
Isn't that girl one of
the students at the school?

381
00:16:46,666 --> 00:16:49,583
What? I don't remember
anyone like this girl.

382
00:16:49,666 --> 00:16:51,125
[REN] She's got an explanation.

383
00:16:51,208 --> 00:16:52,916
She says they haven't
done anything wrong.

384
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,333
Just let 'em go.

385
00:16:55,916 --> 00:16:57,500
[GOZABURO] All right, fine!
I'll release the maggot then.

386
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,625
[GOZABURO] But in return...

387
00:16:59,708 --> 00:17:01,708
[GOZABURO] Take a
turn at bat before ya go.

388
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:02,750
But why?

389
00:17:03,458 --> 00:17:04,708
[GOZABURO]
If he dies on the field,

390
00:17:04,791 --> 00:17:06,458
it'll be treated
like an accident.

391
00:17:06,541 --> 00:17:09,500
But there's no need to
get my own hands dirty.

392
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:15,000
This is bad,
that signal means...

393
00:17:15,083 --> 00:17:17,708
[NAGASUMI] Uh-uh.
It's pretty easy to understand.

394
00:17:17,791 --> 00:17:20,458
[MASA] Nagasumi!
Ya gotta run. Quickly!

395
00:17:20,916 --> 00:17:24,541
[NAGASUMI] Dash!

396
00:17:24,625 --> 00:17:27,250
That oughta teach ya ta
get too full of yerself, maggot!

397
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:29,541
[REN] This is how a
teacher acts? Just pathetic!

398
00:17:29,625 --> 00:17:32,166
[NAGASUMI] Kids,
don't ever try this at home.

399
00:17:38,291 --> 00:17:39,166
[MAWARI THINKS]
What should I do?

400
00:17:39,250 --> 00:17:41,333
If we stay like this, I... No!

401
00:17:41,416 --> 00:17:43,833
Mama would be so
mad at me if I did that.

402
00:17:43,916 --> 00:17:45,083
Think, Mawari!

403
00:17:45,166 --> 00:17:46,500
You can't let yourself
get carried away here.

404
00:17:46,583 --> 00:17:48,500
You want to be Superintendent
General someday.

405
00:17:48,583 --> 00:17:50,791
But, but if we stay like this.

406
00:17:53,041 --> 00:17:56,333
--[KAI GHOST] Mama! Mama!
--[MAWARI] Is he unconscious?

407
00:17:56,416 --> 00:17:58,166
[Mawari cries out]

408
00:17:58,250 --> 00:17:59,750
[MAWARI]
This is why I hate boys!

409
00:17:59,833 --> 00:18:01,166
[CHIMP] My lord.

410
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:06,500
[NAGASUMI] Man. I got beat up.

411
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,333
[NAGASUMI] Hey! Those look good!

412
00:18:08,416 --> 00:18:11,000
[CLASS REP] Yeah?
You think so? Uh.

413
00:18:11,083 --> 00:18:12,500
[MANAGER]
Please, let me help you.

414
00:18:12,583 --> 00:18:13,791
[CLASS REP] I'll take these.

415
00:18:13,875 --> 00:18:16,416
Sure! I'll get some lenses
in them right away!

416
00:18:17,291 --> 00:18:20,208
Well, what did the credit card
company have to say about it?

417
00:18:20,291 --> 00:18:22,250
Approved... We even
contacted the credit card's

418
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:24,500
owner, who said "no problemo."

419
00:18:24,583 --> 00:18:26,291
[MANAGER] This is one
of those cards with such

420
00:18:26,375 --> 00:18:28,875
a high limit it
can even buy a tank!

421
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:31,250
[CLERK] Who is
that boy out there?

422
00:18:31,333 --> 00:18:32,541
All right, young master,

423
00:18:32,625 --> 00:18:34,375
we'll prepare the glasses
for you immediately!

424
00:18:34,458 --> 00:18:36,250
Huh? Young master?

425
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:37,416
--[CLASS REP THINKS] Wow!
