00:21:06,750 --> 00:21:08,875
[MASA] Miss Sun is
of that age, Boss.

495
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:11,833
I'll tell you what...

496
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:14,583
Ask me my name some
other time, and I'll tell you.

497
00:21:14,666 --> 00:21:16,000
I promise I will.

498
00:21:16,083 --> 00:21:17,541
[CLASS REP] Goodbye now!

499
00:21:17,625 --> 00:21:19,125
[NAGASUMI] Hey, wait!

500
00:21:19,208 --> 00:21:21,541
When exactly is
'some other time'?

501
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:24,208
[SUN] In the end,
I guess yesterday

502
00:21:24,291 --> 00:21:26,208
was hardly a
date after all, huh?

503
00:21:26,291 --> 00:21:29,000
Yeah, everything seemed
to get a bit off track.

504
00:21:29,083 --> 00:21:31,083
That reminds me,
Nagasumi, did ya ever

505
00:21:31,166 --> 00:21:32,958
manage to replace
that girl's glasses?

506
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:35,750
Yep. I sure did.
Oh yeah, that's right!

507
00:21:36,375 --> 00:21:37,916
Hey there.

508
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:40,000
Yes? What, what is it?

509
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:41,583
The teacher said
he needed to talk

510
00:21:41,666 --> 00:21:43,708
