511
00:21:44,833 --> 00:21:46,666
Class Rep,
you have to hear this!

512
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:47,958
Oh hey, Class Rep,

513
00:21:48,041 --> 00:21:49,958
have you seen
the attendance book?

514
00:21:50,583 --> 00:21:52,375
[SUN] Oh, Class Rep,
that reminds me.

515
00:21:52,458 --> 00:21:55,333
[CHIMP] Class Rep! Class Rep!

516
00:21:55,416 --> 00:21:56,666
[CLASS REP] I wonder
when someone else

517
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:59,000
will ask what my real name is.

518
00:22:04,458 --> 00:22:09,416
♪

519
00:23:34,416 --> 00:23:35,583
[NAGASUMI]
Yet another transfer student!

520
00:23:35,666 --> 00:23:37,666
Akeno Shiranui,
and she's a real babe!

521
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:38,916
But something's weird.

522
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,500
Oh, so she's connected
to the mermaids, huh?

523
00:23:40,583 --> 00:23:42,875
Well these days it takes a lot
more than that to shock me.

524
00:23:42,958 --> 00:23:45,000
What? What do you mean
'send Sun back to the sea'?

525
00:23:45,083 --> 00:23:46,375
